eign income and assets, and focus heavily on the property as collateral given challenges enforcing loan obligations internationally."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Should You Lock Your Interest Rate Before Construction Begins?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "With construction-to-permanent loans, you lock your permanent mortgage rate at initial closing covering both construction period and conversion to permanent financing\u2014this extended rate lock protects against rate increases during construction but means you won't benefit if rates decline, and extensions create additional costs if construction delays extend beyond your lock period."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How Do Property Taxes Work During Construction?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Do you pay property taxes during construction before the home is habitable? Yes, property taxes continue throughout construction based on land value plus increasing improvement value as construction progresses\u2014most jurisdictions reassess once construction completes, substantially increasing property taxes to reflect the completed home's value."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Can You Live in Your Current Home While Building?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Most borrowers maintain their existing residence during construction, though this creates challenges with carrying two housing payments (current home plus construction loan interest), qualifying within debt-to-income limits with both obligations, timing sale of current home with new construction completion, and managing moving logistics while construction finalizes."}}]};
